<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="1071">
A number spiral is an infinite grid whose upper-left square has number 1. Here are the first five layers of the spiral:<br />
<p><center><img class="invertible" src="/file/bba36f2601b99c7edc15865aa2a49e680a271075f30e86aa0e4e18d00a779c21"></center></p>
Your task is to find out the number in row $y$ and column $x$.<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The first input line contains an integer $t$: the number of tests.<br />
<br />
After this, there are $t$ lines, each containing integers $y$ and $x$.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
For each test, print the number in row $y$ and column $x$.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le t \le 10^5$<br />
<li>$1 \le y,x \le 10^9$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>3<br />
2 3<br />
1 1<br />
4 2</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>8<br />
1<br />
15</code>    </div>
